I'll bet that picture is *before* he took it apart to put the new clamp on, when it was running OK.
No 1 is at 7 o'clock. I'll bet his distributor drive gear is in wrong. As far as his current
problem, he probably doesn't have the distributor shaft engaged in the drive pinion, like Clara
